## In the world of software, most everything takes longer to implement than you expect. And so it's not uncommon to accomplish less in a fixed amount of time than you hope.

### In a sentence (or list of features), define a GOOD outcome for your final project. I.e., what WILL you accomplish no matter what?

A basic tic-tac-toe game that works, and the project has few errors in the rules of tic-tac-toe.


### In a sentence (or list of features), define a BETTER outcome for your final project. I.e., what do you THINK you can accomplish before the final project's deadline?

A unique tic-tac-toe game with a Christmas theme with Christmas game pieces, and the project has little to no errors in the rules of tic-tac-toe.


### In a sentence (or list of features), define a BEST outcome for your final project. I.e., what do you HOPE to accomplish before the final project's deadline?

A unique tic-tac-toe game with the Christmas decorations and Christmas pieces, and the project has no errors at all in the game and piece rules of chess. The game also has a fun Christmas background and plays Christmas music.


## In a paragraph or more, outline your next steps. What new skills will you need to acquire? What topics will you need to research? If working with one of two classmates, who will do what?

First, I will think about and plan exactly what I want my end product to be. I will begin programming by first setting up the tic=tacc-toe board layout and
letting each player select a each piece. Then, I will figure out how to code for knowing what spots are taken and how to save the board progress and display the new board
each round. I will need to research how to code for setting a background image behind the game, as well as how to play background music.
